    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <queue>\n#include <algorithm>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n  int n; cin >> n;\n  vector<vector<int>> g(n);\n  for(int i=0;i<n;i++){int k;cin>>k;g[i].resize(k);for(int j=0;j<k;j++)cin>>g[i][j];}\n\n  // Reverse graph + Kahn\\'s from terminal nodes (out-degree 0)\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nfind-eventual-safe-states:\n  Original graph:\n  0 -> 1 -> 2 -> 5    6\n  |    |\n  2    3\n       |\n       0\n  4 -> 5\n\n  outdeg: [2,2,1,1,1,0,0]\n  Terminal (outdeg=0): 5, 6\n\n  Reverse graph:\n  0 <- 1 <- 2 <- 5    6\n  ^    ^\n  2    3\n       ^\n       0\n  4 <- 5\n\n  Kahn\\'s on reverse: q=[5,6]\n  pop 5 -> indeg[2]--, indeg[4]--\n  pop 6 -> no edges\n  pop 2 -> indeg[1]--\n  pop 4 -> done\n  pop 1 -> indeg[0]--, indeg[3]--\n  pop 0,3 -> done\n\n  Safe: 2,4,5,6 (all nodes processed)\n```\nReverse all edges. Nodes with out-degree 0 in the original graph (terminal nodes) have indegree 0 in the reversed graph. Run Kahn\\'s BFS from these terminal nodes on the reversed graph. Nodes that get processed (reachable from terminals in reverse) are safe, meaning all paths from them eventually lead to terminal nodes. Sort and output. Time O(V+E), Space O(V+E).",
    complexity: {"time":"O(V+E)","space":"O(V+E)"},
    sheet: "LeetCode",
    solution_code: "vector<vector<int>> rg(n); vector<int> outdeg(n); for(int u=0;u<n;u++){outdeg[u]=g[u].size();for(int v:g[u])rg[v].push_back(u);} queue<int> q; for(int i=0;i<n;i++)if(!outdeg[i])q.push(i); vector<int> safe; while(!q.empty()){int u=q.front();q.pop();safe.push_back(u);for(int v:rg[u])if(--outdeg[v]==0)q.push(v);} sort(safe.begin(),safe.end()); for(int x:safe)cout<<x<<\" \";",
