    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <queue>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;\n  string colors; cin >> colors;\n  vector<vector<int>> g(n);\n  vector<int> indeg(n);\n  for(int i=0;i<m;i++){int u,v;cin>>u>>v;g[u].push_back(v);indeg[v]++;}\n\n  // DP + topological sort\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nlargest-color-value:\n  colors: a b a c a\n  Graph: 0→1→2→3→4\n\n  DP table [node][color]:\n  Node 0: a=1\n  Node 1: a=1, b=1  (from 0: a=1, + b=1)\n  Node 2: a=2, b=1  (from 1: a=1+1=2)\n  Node 3: a=2, b=1, c=1\n  Node 4: a=3, b=1, c=1\n\n  Max along all paths: a=3 at node 4\n  Answer: 3\n\n  Cycle case: if cycle exists, return -1\n```\nKahn's algorithm with DP. For each node in topological order, update dp[v][c] = max(dp[v][c], dp[u][c] + (colors[v]==c)). Track max across all nodes. Detect cycle (if processed < n, return -1). Time O((V+E)*26), Space O(V*26).",
