    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <queue>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n  int n; cin >> n;\n  vector<vector<int>> g(n);\n  vector<int> deg(n);\n  for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){int u,v;cin>>u>>v;g[u].push_back(v);g[v].push_back(u);deg[u]++;deg[v]++;}\n\n  // Leaf peeling (topological)\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nminimum-height-trees:\n  0─1─2─3 (chain of 4)\n\n  deg: [1,2,2,1]\n  Step 1: remove leaves 0,3 → deg[1]=1, deg[2]=1\n  Step 2: remove leaves 1,2 → centroids [1,2]\n\n  Star:\n      0\n     /|\\\n    1 2 3\n\n  deg: [3,1,1,1]\n  Step 1: remove leaves 1,2,3 → deg[0]=0 → centroid [0]\n\n  MHT roots are centroids (1 or 2 nodes).\n```\nLeaf peeling (topological sort from leaves). Peel leaves layer by layer. The last 1-2 nodes remaining are centroids (MHT roots). Track degrees, enqueue leaves (deg==1), peel, update neighbor degrees. Time O(V+E), Space O(V+E).",
