    test_cases: [{"input":"5 4\n0 1\n0 2\n1 3\n2 4\n10 20 30 40 50","expected":"4"},{"input":"3 2\n0 1\n1 2\n5 5 5","expected":"1"}],
    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <queue>\n#include <algorithm>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;\n  vector<vector<int>> g(n);\n  vector<int> indeg(n), val(n), dp(n, 1);\n  for(int i=0;i<m;i++){int u,v;cin>>u>>v;g[u].push_back(v);indeg[v]++;}\n  for(int i=0;i<n;i++)cin>>val[i];\n\n  // Kahn's + DP\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nlongest-increasing-path-dag:\n  0[10] → 1[20] → 3[40]\n  ↓\n  2[30] → 4[50]\n\n  DP (longest path ending at node):\n  Initially dp = [1,1,1,1,1]\n\n  Topo: 0,1,2,3,4\n  dp[0]=1\n  dp[1]=max(dp[1], dp[0]+1)=2 (10<20 ✓)\n  dp[2]=max(dp[2], dp[0]+1)=2 (10<30 ✓)\n  dp[3]=max(dp[3], dp[1]+1)=3 (20<40 ✓)\n  dp[4]=max(dp[4], dp[2]+1)=3 (30<50 ✓)\n  max(dp) = 4? Actually path 0→1→3→4 is 4 nodes: 10,20,40,50 → length 4\n\n  Answer: 4\n```\nKahn's algorithm with DP. dp[u] = longest path ending at u. Initialize dp[u]=1. In topological order, for edge u->v, if val[u] < val[v], update dp[v] = max(dp[v], dp[u] + 1). Track max dp. Time O(V+E), Space O(V).",
