    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <queue>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;\n  vector<vector<int>> g(n);\n  for(int i=0;i<m;i++){int u,v;cin>>u>>v;g[u].push_back(v);g[v].push_back(u);}\n\n  // BFS + bitmask DP over subsets\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nshortest-path-all-nodes:\n  Graph: 0─1  2─3\n         │  │  │\n         └──┘  └──\n\n  n=4 (small), use bitmask DP:\n  dp[mask][u] = min steps to reach mask (visited set) ending at u\n\n  Initialize: dp[1<<i][i] = 0 for all i\n\n  BFS from all starting nodes:\n  mask=0001@0 → mask=0011@1(+1) → mask=1011@3(+2) → mask=1111@2(+3) → mask=1111@0(+4)\n  Total: 4 edges\n\n  Final answer: min over dp[1111][i]\n```\nBFS with state (mask, node) where mask tracks visited nodes (n<=12 => 2^12=4096 states). Starting from each node with mask=1<<i. BFS ensures shortest path. Answer is min steps to reach mask = fullMask. Time O(2^n * n^2), Space O(2^n * n).",
