    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nways-to-destination:\n  Graph: 0→1(1), 0→2(2), 1→2(1), 1→3(3), 2→4(1), 3→4(1)\n\n  Dijkstra from 0:\n  dist=[0,∞,∞,∞,∞] ways=[1,0,0,0,0]\n  Pop (0,0): dist[1]=1,w[1]=1; dist[2]=2,w[2]=1\n  Pop (1,1): dist[2]=min(2,1+1=2)=2,w[2]+=w[1]=2; dist[3]=4,w[3]=1\n  Pop (2,2): dist[4]=3,w[4]=2\n  Pop (3,3): dist[4]=min(3,4+1=5)=3\n  Pop (4,4): done\n\n  Answer: ways[4] = 2\n```\nDijkstra with additional ways[] array. When relaxing edge u->v: if dist[u]+w < dist[v], set dist[v]=dist[u]+w, ways[v]=ways[u]. If dist[u]+w == dist[v], ways[v]+=ways[u]. Use modulo 1e9+7. Time O((V+E) log V), Space O(V).",
