    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <queue>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n  int n, target, startFuel; cin >> n >> target >> startFuel;\n  vector<vector<int>> stations(n, vector<int>(2));\n  for(int i=0;i<n;i++)cin>>stations[i][0]>>stations[i][1];\n\n  // Max-heap of fuel at reachable stations\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nrefueling-stops:\n  target=100, startFuel=50\n  stations: 25(25gal), 50(50gal), 75(25gal)\n\n  Current fuel=50, can reach up to 50.\n  Pass station 25 (25gal), add to heap {25}\n  Run out at 50, refuel from heap (max=25), fuel now 25+? = 50, can reach 75+? = wait, let me re-trace:\n\n  Actually: start with 50 fuel.\n  Pass station at 25 (dist 25, fuel 25): add 25 to heap, fuel left = 50-25=25\n  Can't reach station 50 (need 25 more fuel), so refuel: take max from heap = 25, fuel = 25+25=50\n  Reach station 50 (dist 50, fuel 50): add 50 to heap, fuel left = 50-0=50\n  Pass station 75 (dist 75, fuel 25): add 25 to heap, fuel left = 25\n  Can't reach 100 (need 25 more), refuel: take max from heap = 50, fuel = 25+50=75\n  Reach target 100.\n  Total refuels: 2\n```\nGreedy with max-heap. Traverse stations in order, add reachable station fuels to max-heap. When fuel runs out, refuel from heap (largest fuel). If heap empty before target, impossible. Time O(n log n), Space O(n).",
