    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nmax-probability:\n  Graph: 0→1(0.5), 1→2(0.5), 0→2(0.2)\n  Start=0, End=2\n\n  path 0→2: prob=0.2\n  path 0→1→2: prob=0.5*0.5=0.25\n\n  Dijkstra with max-product instead of min-sum:\n  prob[0]=1.0\n  Pop 0: prob[1]=0.5, prob[2]=0.2\n  Pop 1: prob[2]=max(0.2, 0.5*0.5=0.25)=0.25\n\n  Answer: 0.25\n```\nDijkstra variant maximizing product. Use max-heap (or negate probabilities for min-heap). Initialize prob[src]=1.0. When edge u->v, if prob[u]*w > prob[v], update. Use log for stability or just multiply. Time O((V+E) log V), Space O(V+E).",
