    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <queue>\n#include <climits>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n  int n, m, s, t, k; cin >> n >> m >> s >> t >> k;\n  vector<vector<pair<int,int>>> g(n);\n  for(int i=0;i<m;i++){int u,v,w;cin>>u>>v>>w;g[u].push_back({v,w});g[v].push_back({u,w});}\n\n  // Dijkstra with state (node, discountsUsed)\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\ncheapest-route-discount:\n  k=1 discount (halve cost)\n  Edges: 0→1(100), 1→2(100), 2→3(100), 0→3(500)\n\n  Dijkstra with state (node, used):\n  dist[0][0]=0\n  Pop (0,0,0):\n    →(1,0)=100, →(1,1)=50(discount), →(3,0)=500, →(3,1)=250(discount)\n  Pop (1,1,50):\n    →(2,1)=50+100=150, →(2,0)=50+50(discount)=100(wait...)\n  ...\n  Result: min over dist[3][*] = min(dist[3][0]=500, dist[3][1]=250) = 250\n```\nDijkstra over state (node, discountsUsed). For each edge, two transitions: no discount (cost = w) or discount (cost = w/2, used+1). Maintain dist[node][k] = min cost. Answer = min_k dist[t][k]. Time O((V+E)*k*log(V*k)), Space O(V*k).",
    complexity: {"time":"O((V+E)*k*log(V*k))","space":"O(V*k)"},
    sheet: "Striver A2Z",
    solution_code: "vector<vector<int>> dist(n,vector<int>(k+1,INT_MAX)); priority_queue<array<int,3>,vector<array<int,3>>,greater<>> pq; dist[s][0]=0; pq.push({0,s,0}); while(!pq.empty()){auto[d,u,used]=pq.top();pq.pop();if(d>dist[u][used])continue;if(u==t){cout<<d;return 0;}for(auto[v,w]:g[u]){if(dist[u][used]+w<dist[v][used]){dist[v][used]=dist[u][used]+w;pq.push({dist[v][used],v,used});}if(used<k&&dist[u][used]+w/2<dist[v][used+1]){dist[v][used+1]=dist[u][used]+w/2;pq.push({dist[v][used+1],v,used+1});}}}",
