    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nlongest-consecutive-sequence:\n  nums = [100, 4, 200, 1, 3, 2]\n\n  DSU union adjacent numbers:\n  Insert 100: map[100]=100, sz[100]=1\n  Insert 4: map[4]=4\n  Insert 200: map[200]=200\n  Insert 1: map[1]=1, neighbor 0? no, neighbor 2? no → sz=1\n  Insert 3: map[3]=3, neighbor 4 exists! union(3,4) → sz(3)=sz(4)=1+1=2? Actually size 2 now\n  Insert 2: map[2]=2, neighbor 1 exists! union(2,1), neighbor 3 exists! union(2,3) → sz=4\n\n  Max size = 4 (set {1,2,3,4})\n```\nUnion-Find mapping each value to itself. For each value, union with value+1 and value-1 if they exist. Track component size. Return max size. Time O(n * alpha(n)), Space O(n).",
