    test_cases: [{"input":"4\n1 2 3 4\n2 1 4 5\n2\n0 1\n2 3","expected":"2"},{"input":"4\n1 2 3 4\n1 2 3 4\n0","expected":"0"}],
    solution_template: "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <unordered_map>\n#include <algorithm>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main() {\n  int n; cin >> n;\n  vector<int> src(n), dst(n);\n  for(int i=0;i<n;i++)cin>>src[i];\n  for(int i=0;i<n;i++)cin>>dst[i];\n  int m; cin >> m;\n\n  // DSU on indices, compare multisets per component\n\n  return 0;\n}",
    approach: "\n\nDiagram:\n```\nmin-hamming:\n  src=[1,2,3,4], dst=[2,1,4,5]\n  swaps: (0,1), (2,3)\n\n  DSU unions: 0-1, 2-3\n  Component 0: src={1,2}, dst={2,1} → can rearrange to match → 0 diffs\n  Component 2: src={3,4}, dst={4,5} → can match 4 but 3≠5 → 1 diff\n\n  Total Hamming distance = 1+1 = 2\n```\nUnion indices that can be swapped. For each component, count elements in src and dst using multiset/hashmap. Hamming distance per component = number of unmatched elements (sum of absolute differences of frequencies). Sum across components. Time O(n*alpha(n)), Space O(n).",
    complexity: {"time":"O(n*alpha(n))","space":"O(n)"},
    sheet: "Striver A2Z",
    solution_code: "vector<int> par(n); iota(par.begin(),par.end(),0); function<int(int)> find=[&](int x){return par[x]==x?x:par[x]=find(par[x]);}; auto unite=[&](int a,int b){par[find(a)]=find(b);}; for(int i=0;i<m;i++){int a,b;cin>>a>>b;unite(a,b);} unordered_map<int,unordered_map<int,int>> sc,dc; for(int i=0;i<n;i++){int r=find(i);sc[r][src[i]]++;dc[r][dst[i]]++;} int ans=0; for(auto&[r,_]:sc){for(auto&[v,c]:sc[r])ans+=max(0,c-dc[r][v]);} cout<<ans;",
